Subject: [PATCH 2/3] callouts truly outside hero + mobile pricing scale fix
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Move hero callouts OUT of the monitor-panel container (which had
  overflow-hidden from @apply). They're now siblings of the image panel,
  positioned against the .skew-hero wrapper with larger negative offsets
  (-left-[12%] sm, -left-[22%] lg) so they sit beside the screenshot as
  examiner's margin notes, not on top of it.
- Dashed SVG connectors restored on each callout — short horizontal line
  + endpoint dot that visually links the margin note to the image edge.
- On xs viewports (< 640px) the sidebar callouts are hidden; instead a
  stacked list of the three margin notes appears below the hero image so
  nothing is cramped or hidden on mobile.
- "LEVELS OF DEPTH" pricing heading scales responsively
  (text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl) so it fits on narrow viewports.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
